The paper presents a visual active learning system for the extraction of relevant patterns in large high-dimensional datasets. The system uses a small set of user-provided labels to rank similarity measures and calculates an interactive Self-Organizing Map-based relevance model. The approach involves machine learning, computer vision, and information retrieval techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.SI.
